Ryan is 15 and has Asperger's. He's a bit concerned 
about attending his first ever prom, held to mark the end 
of their school lives for year 11 pupils at Passmores

not," he wonders aloud, before asking the film crew, 
individually: "What would you do?" The crew think he 
should go. It's a lovely moment, so typical of this brilliant, 
exemplary, fly-on-the-classroom-wall documentary series. 
Ryan is smashing; happy, keen, funny, clever and 
devoted to headmaster Mr Goddard.
